files/I_have_completed_mandatory_training_Do_I_need_to_do_the_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1693918942 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="I have completed mandatory training Do I need to do the Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="I have completed mandatory training Do I need to do the Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-21_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9f01" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-22_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-24_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-25_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-27_">In the world of care, mandatory training and the Care Certificate are two important aspects that care workers need to be familiar with. While mandatory training covers essential topics and skills necessary for safe and effective care provision, the Care Certificate focuses specifically on the standards and behaviours expected of workers in the health and adult social care sectors. <br><br>In this blog, we will explore the differences between mandatory training and the Care Certificate and whether completing mandatory training exempts one from the requirement of obtaining the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/care-certificate-train-the-trainer-trainer-pack-cpduk-accredited?variant=31839814582341" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Care Certificate</span></i></a>.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-28_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-30_">The difference between mandatory training and the care certificate</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_difference_between_mandatory_training_and_the_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919066" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_difference_between_mandatory_training_and_the_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919066 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_difference_between_mandatory_training_and_the_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1693919066 320w" width="2000" height="1334" alt="The difference between mandatory training and the care certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The difference between mandatory training and the care certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-31_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-34_">When it comes to mandatory training and the Care Certificate, it's important to understand the distinctions between the two. While mandatory training typically covers essential topics and skills that care workers, need to perform their roles safely and effectively, the Care Certificate focuses specifically on the standards and behaviours expected of workers new in the health and adult social care sectors.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-35_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-37_">Completing mandatory training </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Completing_mandatory_training_-_Do_I_need_the_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919448" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Completing_mandatory_training_-_Do_I_need_the_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919448 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Completing_mandatory_training_-_Do_I_need_the_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1693919448 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Completing mandatory training - Do I need the Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Completing mandatory training - Do I need the Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-38_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-39_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-41_">If you have completed mandatory training, it means that you have met the requirements set by your organisation or regulatory body (the Care Quality Commission for those in England) for essential training topics such as infection control, health and safety, safeguarding, and more. This training is necessary to ensure you have the foundational knowledge and skills for your role in healthcare.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-42_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-44_">Standards and expectations for care workers</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Standards_and_expectations_for_care_workers_-_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919488" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Standards_and_expectations_for_care_workers_-_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919488 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Standards_and_expectations_for_care_workers_-_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1693919488 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Standards and expectations for care workers - Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Standards and expectations for care workers - Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-45_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-46_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-48_">On the other hand, the Care Certificate is a separate set of 15 standards that defines the minimum expectations of workers in health and social care roles. It encompasses areas such as communication, privacy and dignity, duty of care, safeguarding, and person-centered care. A Care Certificate can only be issued once all of its 15 standards are completed. The completion of the Care Certificate demonstrates that you possess the necessary skills, knowledge, and behaviours to provide compassionate and high-quality care to individuals.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-51_">Importance of completing the Care Certificate</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Importance_of_completing_the_Care_Certificate_-_Online_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919671" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Importance_of_completing_the_Care_Certificate_-_Online_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1693919671 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Importance_of_completing_the_Care_Certificate_-_Online_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1693919671 320w" width="2000" height="1377" alt="Importance of completing the Care Certificate - Online training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Importance of completing the Care Certificate - Online training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-52_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-53_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-55_">While mandatory training may cover some of the same topics as the Care Certificate, it does not replace the need to complete the Care Certificate. The Care Certificate provides a standardised framework for assessing and verifying workers' competence in specific 